gomodel:SYNGO_4643  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2. Confocal imaging of cultured mouse hippocampal neurons at DIV14 that were double-immunostained for TLCN (ICAM5) and MAP-2 (dendritic marker), show localization of TLCN (ICAM5) on dendritic filopodia.\n\nFigure 4f,j. Analogously, triple-immunostaining for TLCN (ICAM5), PSD95 (DLG4) and synaptophysin (SYP) at DIV14,21,28 shows partial overlap that suggests postsynaptic localization.\n\nFigure 4o,p. \"Double immunostaining of Bassoon (magenta) and TLCN (green). At 14 DIV, Bassoon-positive presynaptic clusters are frequently apposed to TLCN-positive filopodia.\"\n\nFigure 4s,t. \"Double immunostaining of GABAA receptor (magenta) and TLCN (green). Clusters of GABAA receptor show no correlation with TLCN localization at both 14 DIV (S) and 21 DIV (T).\". Experimental description: \"Mouse hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared essentially as described previously (Okabe et al., 1999, 2001).\"\n\n\"The antibodies used were as follows:\nrabbit polyclonal anti-TLCN recognizing the cytoplasmic tail peptide of TLCN (1:5000) (Sakurai et al., 1998);\nmouse monoclonal anti-TLCN recognizing the extracellular epitope of only rabbit TLCN (clone 271A6; 1:3000) (Mori et al., 1987);\nguinea pig polyclonal anti-TLCN/Fc recognizing the extracellular region of TLCN (1:3000) (S. Mitsui, M. Saito, K. Mori, and Y. Yoshihara, unpublished observations);\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4643" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

